The paper deals with the problem of leader election in distributed computing, which is a fundamental problem in the field of distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem is studied in the context of anonymous trees, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between the allocated time and the amount of information given to the nodes, which involves information theory (cs.IT). The problem of leader election also has applications in network engineering (cs.NE) and social networks (cs.SI).
